# Baseline

- Read the README and existing code before large changes. Match project style.
- Minimize diff scope. Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Never commit secrets (.env, tokens, keys). Warn if asked to commit them.
- Only create git commits when the user asks.
- Run the project's existing lint/build/test scripts when you change code.
- If `.cursor/skills/` exists in this repo, read relevant skills before implementing.
- Definition of done: changes in the real repo branch, not a scratchpad or uncommitted local-only work.
